  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a ti-leaf-wrapped ttukbaegi earthenware-cook over medium heat.",
    "Sear beef cubes until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove beef and set aside.",
    "Add onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, cumin powder, turmeric, cayenne pepper, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add chickpeas, chickpeas liquid, tomato paste, and chicken broth. Stir to combine.",
    "Return beef to pot and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until beef is tender.",
    "Stir in diced tomatoes and cook for an additional 10 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley.",
    "Let tagine rest for 10 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or couscous, if desired."
  ],
